  "title": "Electrical_Thermal_FingerTapping_2015",
  "description": "This dataset comprises near-infrared spectroscopy (NIRS) measurements of hemodynamic brain responses during painful and non-painful finger-tapping stimulation. The study investigates the specificity of cerebral blood flow changes to noxious stimuli using functional NIRS, with concurrent assessment of autonomic responses. Data were collected from multiple participants undergoing controlled thermal and electrical stimulation protocols.",
  "methods_description": "Functional near-infrared spectroscopy (fNIRS) was used to measure hemodynamic responses during finger-tapping tasks with thermal and electrical stimulation. Short separation regression was applied to improve statistical localization of hemodynamic responses and account for varying autonomic responses across stimulation conditions.",
